caption: Delicious food and great service! Go to place for signature NOLA Brunch!!
Food was excellent.  Great service. Cash only. ATMs on site.
The grits and sausage were phenomenal. We loved it all
Worst food I have ever eaten in New Orleans , shrimp and grits was disgusting.. service horrible, mgr. rude
One of the best places i.went to wile I was in town and the live music was out of this world.

2nd review of this place! 3rd time coming, glad to see the same manager that has always seated us here. Same excellent food, same excellent service. The place was PACKED on this trip, not an available seat, and we were still welcomed and seated quickly, the service was still faster than just about anywhere else! Please don't lose your cooks or your management! You guys are crushing it!!! Will always visit each time we are here. We love this place♡♡♡
Great food right at the square. Fantastic bloody Mary, and if you are indecisive order the trio! Enjoy!
An amazing place to eat! The staff is so welcoming and the food is delicious!
Our waiter tried to short change us on our bill. We called him out on it and he quickly had our change . He for sure has done this before . Watch your money there . !
The food and the service was outstanding. And the coffee was really good too! 10/10 recommend
We stopped in for brunch our first day in town and have been every day since, great food, great drinks, and even better service! Will definitely be back again when we come to town!
Prices are reasonable, lots of food, and tastes amazing!!
Delicious! Definitely going to be a regular stop!
Great place! Wonderful menu selection. The brunch po boy was so good. The bread was amazing. Delicious drinks for brunch. Erin, our server was super nice.

Although being directly on Jackson Square makes it seem like a touristy thing, Monty's has one of my favorite breakfasts in the city. The beignet fries are absolutely to die for along with the eggs benedict always being perfect. There's a discount for locals as well.

Was not amused. One, the food is just too expensive for breakfast. I understand they have to pay rent but there was nothing special about the food. Secondly, they fail to properly tell you that they are cash only. When I brought this up to somebody, they told me there were signs outside that said so. The sign is at the door in small lettering right by your feet. Why would I have looked there? Therefore, I had to use their atm ($4 charge) to pay for my meal. I am a college student who is just trying to keep a small budget on my trip. Nevertheless, our waiter was very friendly.
Perfection
Would like too see more information about the food on the menu. Plus pork substitution on breakfast options
So beautiful out
Food was good. Service was ok. Cash only.
I had the greatest Po-Boy ever! No matter the time of day get the Breakfast Po-Boy!
Biggest chicken breast I've ever seen on a sandwich Food was excellent! The place was crowded but we were treated like we were the only people in the restaurant Great value for breakfast and brunch!
Great food. Bloody Mary was different but good all in all. Fun atmosphere and great service!
Great service and breakfast!

This place is amazingly good. The service is friendly and attentive. The food came out hot and fast. The restaurant was clean and well taken care of. The only downside is that it is indoor seating only. It you hit a pocket where the restaurant is mostly empty, you will be good to go.
Beinget fries are out of this world!  Everything else is amazing too
Definitely needs a revamp on FOH staff! Otherwise nice place!
Best beignets I’ve ever had in New Orleans!! The Salted Carmel Coffee was great too and the carnivore omelet!!
stopped in for a quick lunch, alligator sausage Po Boy was the Bomb!
Excelente food. $$. Customers services Excelente, however they want you to finish fast because the need your table. The supervisor mistake.  The rest  it is a food place for breakfast
Alcohol pricey but food makes it worth it.
Great place for a made from scratch Hurricane and also a pitcher a of Mimosas. Definitely will come back when NOLA again.

I absolutely love this place. Ita a must go everytime we come to New orleans. The food is amazing and the staff is even better. The manager(?) I think, is so beyond nice and accommodating. He has gone out of his way to make us feel so welcome everytime we are there. I highly recommend this place to anyone who comes to New orleans!

Best breakfast I think I've ever had. The guy who i believe is the owner or manager was friendly and accommodating. He recognized us from coming in a few days before and gave us a 20% off voucher. The grits are on another level and the crab cake Benedict can't be beat. Amazing.

Monty's was amazing!!!! If I could give it 10 stars I would. The service was phenomenal, it did not take a long time for us to recieve our food. They were not overly priced and to be honest it wouldn't surprise if they raised the prices the food, experience, and service is just that great. If you are looking for a great drink try the Monty Tai all you need is one trust me. The crawfish macaroni and cheese is to die for. Love this place and is one of the best things about New Orleans.
such a long queue hahahaha
Excellent breakfast 🥞👍👍
What is all on your loaded fries? We ate there 5 years ago & they were Amazing!!! I live in Alabama & would love to make me some, even though they won’t be as good as yours😊

Everything, and I mean everything that we ate was delicious. My boyfriend and I celebrated his birthday brunch here and were delighted by everything we ate; beignet fries, mimosas, crab cake benedict, chicken and biscuits. We'll for sure stop here again on our next trip to the Big Easy.
Place was closed due to COVID-19. Only went there because we like NCIS New Orleans. Only way we knew it was the place besides Google, was the front doors.
Brunch was great. The drinks were great! Dustin was our server both times and he was so amazing! 😍
Stopped here before we headed out to explore the city. Great place to have brunch.
Brunch menu was on point

I had  a breakfast dish today and I was not pleased. I Did not eat it. I was going to pay for it regardless but they took it off my bill .  Now if you really want Somewhere good to eat I suggest you go to stanley's .  Not far from there and the food is excellent.

Recently visited and the food was bland and had no taste. Someone at my table had crawfish mac & cheese and it was like cheese soup. My pizza had no taste to the sauce. Out server wasn’t the greatest either. Best thing was the Beignet fries!
Amazing food and management and staff were so polite and hospitable . This is our second time coming while we are visiting New Orleans and it’s definitely now our food must have .
We wondered upon this place across the street from Cafe Du Mond. Service was quick and friendly. Food was delicious and fresh.
TOURIST TRAP. Stay away. Watered down drinks. Flat sodas. Laminated reusable menus not wiped down. Guard your health. Cash only sign not clearly posted, like other signs. Overrated food.
Amazing service! Definitely recommend ❤️
Good service, good food!
I enjoyed a good burger here and the staff was friendly. Laid back atmosphere.
Their food was so good. Great spot to eat while watching Jackson Square come to life. The King's Cake beignets were my favorite beignets of the trip.
Biscuits and gravy are great
Had breakfast, great food. Poboy was amazing. Drinks were a perfect morning treat.
An amazing breakfast. Best grits I've ever had. The beignet fries were awesome. The style makes it so much easier to eat and share. Service was also great. Looking forward to going back.

I went there for brunch. It was very busy, the customer service left for something to be desired. I got the beignet fries and French toast. The French toast was bland and unimpressive but the beignet fries were amazing, now this is a controversial take but I liked them better than the beignets you could get all over the city.

Just walking by and decided to eat here. It was fantastic. Waitstaff was so nice and welcoming and food came in just a few minutes. Food was excellent and bacon had so much flavor. Very happy with our choice to eat here.
Fire! My next time in NOLA I’m coming here first.

We didn't actually eat there. The service was impeccable but the mimosas had a really gross smell and after taste. I was excited that they had pitchers but ended up having to power through and gag them down.
Ordered crab cake Egg Benedict and was not disappointed! Really have nothing bad to say about this place. Worth the visit, much easier to be waited on than across the street.
Delicious food and great drinks.

Ordered their southern breakfast and the chicken seemed like it was recooked. Definitely not freshly fried chicken. It wouldn’t even cut properly. Informed the server and he said maybe it was that one piece.. won’t recommend this place.
Food was decent. Management rushed us out after the meal as my party was having coffee... wouldn’t come back
It is a charming restaurant with very good food for a fair price. It is also a nice alternative for the Cafe Du Monde where there are usually long lines.
Friendly, quick service. Great breakfast menu.
Amazing food with great service. Couldn't have been better. King cake beignets!
Better beignets and coffee than that overrated place across the street with the line out the door. No waiting for a window table, Excellent service.

Great brunch spot. Very busy on weekends. For a reason the food is delicious recommend the beignet fries. Also had the eggs Benedict which was very delicious. A bloody also complements the meal nicely.
Very good portion sizes.
Good food. Come early for no line, now wait
Excellent service ! Get the Jambalaya Omelette with pepper jack cheese and thank me later ! Delicious!
The food is okay. If they ask do you want a drink to go after you have your ticket. Be ware you will get a new ticket with a higher price. Unless it's soda.

Great little place at Jackson Square. The portions were huge! The food was delicious. Price extremely fair for a tourist attraction. If you can’t finish your meal, get it to go and hand it to a homeless person. You can see the street performers while you eat and take in the entire New Orleans experience from your table.

My 1st experience here was 3 years ago. They serve the best cheese grits that I've ever eaten and did not have to add anything, by way of seasoning to it! Here it is 3 years later, I'm visiting the beautiful city of New Orleans again with a fantastic group of friends and Monty's on the Square, did not disappoint with the cheese grits! Thanks so much we will be back!!
Good food and service.
Best eggs benedict with hollandaise in Nola

While on vacation in New Orleans it was hard to get in anywhere, but this place didn’t have long lines. My boyfriend had a brunch Poboy sandwich which he can’t get over and wants to visit again just to have another one! I had king cake beignets which were sweet and wonderful! Loved this place❤️

Really just ok. The gumbo cup i got (glad i didnt get the bowl) had no distinguishing taste or textures. Just pepper. Black pepper. The pecan bundt cake was just whiskey soaked cake with melting whip cream
Great food, good price, good service
Good service and food was average. Found it to be overpriced for flavor and amount of food. Rice and beans with chicken was good. Gumbo and crawfish Mac and cheese was ok. Not worth the money.
Good food and a great server (Travis, I think?)

Wonderful... great coffee, great beignet fries, the best service. I was seated immediately and watched the line around the block across the street at Cafe du Monde. Skip the line, Monty's will hook you up.

Food was good, but the service was absolutely horrible. We had a pretty decent size group coming and a few was late. We were constantly told if our guess did not come that they were going to take our table away and the guy seem to be irritated which was so annoying!! And it was also as if we were being rushed. So if you visit here make sure your whole party is together because if not, you will be constantly reminded of how late they are and how they need the tables!!!

Today was my mom's birthday and it was the most terrible experience I ever had.  They rushed my whole party and didn't give anyone time to order what they wanted. Plus they came to our table mutiple times saying they were going to take away our extra table because the last 3 guests weren't present.  I literally was in tears because I didn't know how to react to the rushed service, disrespect and unprofessionalism.  It was our first time here and I am never coming back.
Great in house bloody Mary's.
Red beans and rice was slamming!!! Service, good ol southern hospitality, new awleans style!!
I ate breakfast here an omelette, biscuits and gravy, and grits. Best breakfast I had in a long time. The grits were just the way I like them buttery and lots of cheese. 😁😁
Great breakfast
Very good food. Everything on the menus I have tried was good
Great brunch and views of the Square and Cafe du Monde. Very attentive service.
Wonderful food & drinks. Friendly & helpful staff.
Food was good. The king cake beignets were asome.
The service was great and the food was delicious. I recommend the jambalaya. With sausage.
Great service.

Best way to start out your day in The Big Easy!  We stayed at a fantastic hotel nearby and began our mornings/days at Monty's...food is phenomenal, staff is friendly as all get out, and the ambience there early a.m. is comforting but at the same time creates a buzz/excitement for the day ahead.  To Nicky & Britt - thanks again...we loved starting out our mornings with you all. Take care.

This was my first time in New Orleans. I wasn't prepared for how overwhelming, crowded and expensive other restaurants were, ($12 for a grilled cheese sandwich) or their "cash only" policies. I was so glad to come across Monty's. The prices were not outrageous like some of the other places around. The interior was calm, clean, and beautiful with helpful and kind servers (Dusty may have been his name?) that were not going in for the "hard sell" like most of the people we encountered that day as we were walking around. Monty's was truly a calm in the storm and a little bit of familiarity mixed with an authentic New Orleans experience. The food was amazing! I had the crawfish mac and cheese, my friend had some gumbo and we took home some bread pudding. The only tiny things that bothered me was the sweet tea was lemon flavored and the windows had no type of shades to block the harsh direct sunlight from beaming in on us. It's definitely a place I will plan to visit again! Thank you for not being "cash only" lol

Not sure how this place is so highly rated. I wasn’t impressed with anything. My omelette was bland and the potatoes were dry and overcooked. I sampled my friends’ food and their items were also uninspiring. The server lacked personality. I wouldn’t recommend this place and I’m okay with never returning.
Our group of 8 had brunch here and had great service and food. We had to wait a while to be seated, but it was a weekend. The red beans and rice are top notch here.
Great breakfast. Highly recommend the crab cake benedict.
Best eggs Benedict (crab was my favorite!) My husband's was great, too!!

Dustin was amazing. I work in the service industry and tend to be ‘unconsciously’ judge mental of service timing and standards.  He exceeded my standards within minutes of greeting us and maintained his attentiveness throughout our experience.

This is a great spot for breakfast that is close to a lot of the action with Cafe Du Monde right across the way. Food was good and my mimosas were on point. Our waiter was the absolute best!!! I feel so bad that I forgot his name; I’ll put that on the yummy mimosas he kept bringing me! 😋🥂
Breakfast was very good, definitely recommend this place for a tasty breakfast!
Great food.  I was very impressed with the gumbo and my wife was raving about the shrimp and grits.  The space is a little tight but not bad.  We ate at the bar and had a very nice experience
Dustin was cool! Food was fabulous
Great place! Great service!
An epic place for hot chocolate and Beignet.Extremely popular. Street musicians serenade you as you sip in coffee or hot chocolate
Beignet fries were freaking delicious!! Service was quick! Great place to go!!
Awesome
The drinks are refreshing and the food is delicious!
Great food and service
Great food and service
(Translated by Google) Good breakfasts ...  (Original) Buenos desayunos...

Great place for breakfast. On the square just across from Cafe Dumonde but with AC and no line. They have eggs Benedict and beignet fries and morning cocktails. Just sit back and enjoy a bloody mary with breakfast and watch the tourists across the street. Also have fried green tomato Benedict.
Everything was great!
(Translated by Google) Highly!!! Must visit!  (Original) Очень!!!  Must visit!

The omlett I had was great with plenty of flavor. However, the waiter didn't take my gluten intolerance concerns seriously even though I directly stated I would get sick if I eat gluten. He made no suggestions other than yes, I can order eggs but was unwilling to verify info for me. He offered several sides and I chose potatoes and asked if they were plain as I was concerned about gluten hidden in seasonings and the waiter stated yes. When the food came the potatoes were deep fried (I can only assume there isn't a dedicated fryer some this was never stated). I pushed the potatoes to the side. I was hungry ate the omlett and ended up not getting sick but feel that intolerances and allergies are not taken seriously at this restaurant and for that reason wouldn't return. There are many other options in this city that take concerns seriously and have excellent food. Sad because I think the food is good. I was here last year and had beignet fries and those were good too (before I learned I have Celiac).
Yum
This restaurant is Stylish  and provides delicious foods
Great service,  delicious food

I had the French toast and it was excellent. Really good flavor.i added strawberries; however, they give you very few for the money. I'd skip the strawberries as it's more of a garnish than a topping.

Definitely deserving of 4-stars. My friends and I went here simply because the cafe across the street had a ridiculous line. With that said, we were glad that we went to Monty's. The service was quick. Our waitress was friendly and accommodating. The food, most importantly, was delicious. We had the pancakes, the beignets, the French toast, the eggs, the sausage, loads of bacon, mimosas, bellinis, orange juice, the salted caramel coffee, and cranberry juice. I would recommend all of those, but note it is a lot of food.
(Translated by Google) It is a place full of lyrical artists, very atmosphere and very hot  (Original) Es un lugar lleno de artistas líricos mucho ambiente y muy caluroso
The food was awesome and service couldn't have been better, very nice and polite.
Look at those pictures, need I say more?
Great as usual
Great Jackson Square Omlette, but the biscuits were hard as a rock.
Tourist trap gallore.  Overpriced, mediocre food.
Do not waste your time here. Food is overly priced for the amount/quality.

Can’t get a spot at the Cafe du Monde or don’t feel like waiting 3+ hours for a plate of beignets? Just walk across the street to Monty’s on the Square. We were sat down right away for a cup of coffee and some brunch. We wound up getting a plate of the King Cake Beignets, which were absolutely amazing. They’re coated in the traditional powdered sugar, but filled with a cinnamon sugar mixture. Almost similar to a cinnamon bun, but somehow better. Would highly recommend ordering a plate of these!
Great music outside! The drummers are amazing and so talented.
Nice food and atmosphere
Great atmosphere and food

This place is amazing. We had the king cake beignets, the jambalaya with green beans, and fried chicken and the shrimp platter. The beignets were hot, fresh, and filled with cinnamon. The jambalaya had just the right amount of seasoning and the rice was not over cooked. The shrimp were fresh and paired perfectly with the remoulade sauce. The service is wonderful and the atmosphere was very pleasant.
Great experience and good food. MAKE SURE YOU GET LLOYD AS YOUR WAITER 👍🏾👍🏾👍🏾👍🏾
Great place.

(Translated by Google) Perfect if you don't want to wait for the long lines of Cafe du Monde, good quality, good prices and excellent staff treatment  (Original) Perfecto si no quieres esperar las largas colas de Cafe du Monde, buena calidad, buenos precios y el trato del personal excelente
Tried my first ever gumbo and loved it
A nice bar with good food for any meal and excellent drinks.  However, their Jackson Square Omlette is worth a visit!
Excellent crab cake Benedict for breakfast with amazing cheese Grits! Great service too!
Busy, and when you eat, you see why. Excellent service, great food and drink.
Food was delicious 👌. Definitely worth it.
They treat you like VIPs
Staff are excellent, kind, and fast. Fantastic food and a nice place to take a break from all the shops.

Monty’s was a great place to eat! The staff was super friendly and the food came out fast! It’s inside so it’s nice and cool which is a blessing in the Louisiana heat! It’s right across cafe du monte so you can hear the locals playing music outside! We loved Monty’s so much we eat breakfast there every morning of our trip!!
Great little stop for breakfast right next Jackson Square! The beignet fries, king cake beignets and delicious 'spiced' coffee drinks were all amazing! The staff was friendly and service was prompt!
We have ate at Monty's twice on our four day visit and they have not disappointed us! Their bloody Mary's and the big easy eggs Benedict are out of this world!

We went to this cute little spot for breakfast  and it did not let us down. We order the private club po'boy with side eggs and bacon. It was so big and delicious! Enough for two for sure. Our server was very sweet and attentive and we had a great view too. It was just perfect!
Friendly and attentive service in a great location. Had the biscuits and gravy with sausage - wow!
Great  food. Great service. I had the shrimp platter. It was great.

The Beignets made in fries Style are freaking genius. Not only are the bed sizes are also crispy it's a super easy to handle. I believe this is the best way to enjoy Beignets if you ask me. Will go there again just for those
The food was good but pricey
Food was delicious! Their chicken gumbo was delicious as was their crab cakes.
Wonderful sandwich
Great location and food, service needs work. Seems like employees have a lack of motivation.

Short wait, food was quickly prepared. And our waitress was very nice. I didn't like the way my omelette was prepared and the waitress quickly and happily took it back to and I ordered something else that came out great. Overall wonderful experience.
Milk Punch! Holy yum! So good. Great place to take a break from the heat and grab a drink. Came here with my parents last week. We went to Monty's twice for the Milk Punch.
Friendly, cozy atmosphere.
Awesome, I suggest you get the Breakfast Po-Boy.

Went to brunch here last Saturday around 11:45. Although the Jackson Square area was packed with tourists, we only waited 15 minutes. The servers were very friendly, knowledgeable, and eager to make suggestions for our visit. The food was delicious and came out impressively fast!

Honestly not a big fan. Had a party of 6 and we all got different items which none of us really enjoyed. The Muffuletta which I had was pretty bland and not what you would expect. The burger wasn't good at all, looks like they used frozen patties.The Po'boy sandwiches were not well received either. Overall, the service was fine but the food was terrible and overpriced for the quality.

The pizza was ok, but the burger and the muffuletta was NOT impressive in any way. It reminded me of school cafeteria food. You could tell it was frozen food that had been reheated. I would not recommend Monty’s on the Square.

Right on Jackson Square (across from Cafe du Monde). Had the perfect New Orleans breakfast here: Beignet Fries w/powdered sugar and coffee, New Orleans Benedict (add fried green tomatoes and Cajun Hollandaise sauce to the normal), with side of grits. The server was attentive despite the breakfast crowd you’d expect at this tourist location.
The place stunk

Great breakfast stop! Right off Jackson square with lots of yummy brunch options. Had the crab cake Benedict and was delicious. A friend had the pancakes which were amazing! Get's super busy on the weekends so try to come during the week so you don't have to wait!
Not good service and the food is terrible. Uneatable! Would keep away.
Graet breakfast place  the wait is a bit but you know what when you get in great food so worth the time ..great service.
Enjoyed the food here very spacious and amazing service!
Really enjoyed it the mgr was every where. Service was quick and the place was packed
Too cramped
Great place for brunch in the French Quarter. I recommend the jambalaya omelette and the pancakes.
Great breakfast
Had breakfast here two days in a row because it was so good- the caramelized onions in the omelets were so tasty! My husband liked the French toast.

Love this place! French toast and Jackson Square omelet were impeccable! Great place to eat and our server Tristan was amazing! A party of 5 is considered a large party and gratuity will be added fyi.
Great French toast and open air dining! Lots of opportunities for people watching
Great corner spot for people watching. Had great service. Drank wine and hot tea. Ordered beignet fries which were stunning!
Staff need to look a little smarter by all wearing a recognizable uniform. Food OK
Good drinks, but bartenders were eating  behind the bar, then making drinks without washing their hands that they just had in their mouths, which is why we didn't order food.. disappointing.
(Translated by Google) Beigenet Freeze!  (Original) Beigenet Frys!
Nice quality cocktails at a reasonable price for NOLA.
Their breakfast poboys are excellent. Service is great, everyone there is nice. This was a good ending to our trip to NOLA.
Drinks and food good, service exelent!
Tristan was an awesome server. Food yummy, ambience perfect!
Great service & location

Came in on Sunday with 3 other people before leaving out of town and no one was crazy about their food..the gravy on the po boys needs work ..the seafood omelet barely had any seafood and was tasteless and I had to send my pancakes back because they were burnt .who burns pancakes and send them out...its definitely not worth what they are charging for the food.
Breakfast for six, really enjoyed the whole experience!
Food was good. Atmosphere was awesome! A little loud but your in NOLA.

I had read reviews from earlier and figured we would try it out for some New Orleans favs. To be honest location is great ...lively atmosphere outside, but the place does need some updating. Service was polite but really slow. Ordered the chicken and sausage gumbo ..half order..it was a small cup and luke warm. It was flavorful I guess, but not what you might expect from southern cooking. The shrimp Po-boy was definitely lacking something...maybe some more seasoning or sauce? Overall not bad ...but nothing memorable considering the cost and slow service. Sorry...maybe I just had higher expectations.
The service was really good. Food was EXCELLENT! Huge portion size.
Great Food. Highly Recommend.
Excellent food and atmosphere
Fast service, great staff, great food. Right on Jackson Square so you can enjoy the music and artists during lunch.
The food was "okay". It was a little pricey and our waiter was not real pleasant. :(
The crab cake Benedict is awesome
Delicious! Great service!
This was the best breakfast I had in New Orleans. I even think there food is better then the Ruby Slipper. Great taste and favor.
Service was AMAZING!! Lloyd was very friendly and kept our coffee topped up! The alligator sausage poboy we had was delicious. Will definitely return here the next time we're in the Quarter! Thanks!!

Enjoyed brunch here! Country breakfast was delicious! Great atmosphere, right across from Jackson Square and Cafe Du Monde. Loved the large, open windows. Staff was a tad slow, but it was Mardi Gras, so we expected that.
I dream about the brunch po boy.  Can be a bit pricey but worth every penny.  Go there now!

The food, especially the beignets is better than ANY other location!  Beignets are best served with something in the middle!  The other stand out quality is the service, in particular, the server Lloyd.  He was spectacular!!!  You have to give kudos to the staff that can deal with Mardi Gras crowds!  No sweat for him!!!

$$$+ Very good food, service was fast and courteous. Atmosphere was very pleasant as well. A bit pricy. Another of N'Oleans great eateries. You must try the house Bloody Mary! Highly recommended  PLEASE LIKE my review if it has been helpful to you. Thanks!
After spending the afternoon walking through the Quarter Monty's was a great place to stop and have dinner. Our waiter, Kenneth, was the best!
Amazing food and great service! If you are there during Carnival season, make sure you get the King Cake Beignets. I wish I could have those shipped to me. That's how good they are.
Food and service wad good. Far too much food though, they did offer to box up the remaining. Probably will visit again.
Great for late brunch, Crab cakes Benedict a must!
We had the Shrimp and grits and the Jambalaya. Both were excellent. I would recommend it.
Best breakfast and lunch!!! Cajun Benedict is always a good choice to fight off a hangover!!!
Very Nice local eatery
Good breakfast
Perfect location, especially for people watching. It used to be the River's Edge Cafe and the food is a little different. Good for a quick meal with friends, nice bar area.

Really enjoyed the food here. Service was outstanding. I know this may not be the quintessential place to eat in New Orleans, but I really enjoyed the grits here. My wife got a burger and said it was very good.  I would return. They have a nice bar here as well.

We were walking in Jackson square when the rain came in so we ducked in and had a couple of excellent drinks to pass the time.  The  Bartender was very friendly and the staff were  Awesome.I was very impressed with all the people that were there for lunch and I could tell they were having an excellent time.
AMAZING!! Had 30 mins to eay, called ahead and they had our food waiting for us! Tasted phenomenal!!

Travis and the whole staff made us feel like family. The food and drinks  were delicious and generous! We will be back next time we are in New Orleans. Do yourself a favor and have the  King cake beignets. Oh my!
Great breakfast . love those beignet fries !

The hubby and I made a quick stop in New Orleans on our way to Batin Rouge. After a fun evening enjoying the night life, Monty’s was a wonderful cure to a hangover with mimosas and the most incredible eggs Benedict I’ve ever eaten.

Right across from Cafe Du Monde but definitely shouldn't be overlooked. Google Rating online of 4.1 stars is pretty accurate.  The food was pretty good and service was very fast.  We had the traditional eggs and french toast. The eggs came with bacon and potatoes. The potatoes were very good. French toast was very good too. Reasonable prices for the area.
Amazing. Dont understand anything less than 5 stars.
Quick service and strong drinks , lol made my horse and carriage tour much more interesting didn't try the food but the menu looked tasty nice spot on jackson good service
Great spot. Amazing food and friendly staff. Nice ambience.

I can’t comment on the dining experience here, but just stopping by for a few drinks was a good experience. Our bartender Jordan was very welcoming and friendly, and our drinks hit the spot after a much needed break during our walk back to our hotel.
Beer was good, but food not so much. Bathrooms are filthy!

This place was great for a quick breakfast and back to exploring the streets.  If your looking for a good priced breakfast and a spot to people watch, this is it. All the trolley tours are here and the square is great for relaxing and taking a break.
Great Crab Cakes Benedict and Pizzas

It's been a year and I still wouldn't eat at this place.  Just a reminder there's a lot of great restaurants in New Orleans and this is NOT one of them!  I can't imagine anyone having a good experience here.  Most likely the worst service ever.  It was so bad I thought I was on an episode of "What Would You Do."  I'd starve to death before depending on a meal from this place.  Do yourself a HUGE favor and spend your money elsewhere!

Great food and service!

We were so happy to go here but was extremely dissapointed mainly at the service and the food. Our server Kenneth was very rude and not welcoming, he never asked us how our food was, he was carrying plates in front of us without asking if we were done, and had a nasty attitude throughout the whole service, not one smile. We could not wait to leave The food was also dry and none of us like our food except the fries. will not be returning, we had better service everywhere else we went except this place.

Based on reviews, we chose this place for breakfast.  Again, very disappointed!  The only saving grace was the Bloody Mary's.  They were excellent! Best ones we had in Nola.  Food, cold.  Service slow, slow and slower.  I got the crab Benedict.   Very little Hollandaise and it had a film on it when it arrived.  Crab cakes were full of filler and very little crab.  Biscuit was good, but the whole presentation was terrible.  Taste marginal.  Overall, highly disappointed.  Service horrendous, extremely slow.

What lovely service.  Also, considering the ridiculously over-hyped shop (complete with ridiculously long line) across the street, this place is an easy and more-than-acceptable go-to.  No fancy coffee available here.  I debated ordering their "beignet fries", but decided that was a bit on the nose. So I went with their brunch po' boy - French bread, bacon, fried green tomatoes, over-medium eggs, remoulade, and lettuce. And a side of cheesy grits.  The bread was toasted, but obviously from yesterday. Remoulade tasted more like mustard than anything else. Sandwich was decidedly messy to eat (who wants messy food? Not me). And the grits were pasty rather than creamy. Still, it was tasty despite the inadequacies.  And, as I said, the service was fast and friendly.
Stopped for a quick refreshment. It's a pretty nice place, especially taking into account the location.

Me and my wife sat at the bar and were taken care of by Jordan. She was incredibly friendly, very knowledgeable hand gave us some incredible places to visit throughout our honeymoon. Food was great, chicken tenders especially.
Great breakfast, avoid peak hours it's busy on the square
Amazing food and great service. We're trying to try a different restaurant every time we eat, but we would come back here without hesitation.
Loved the food, the alligator sausage pizza was really good and the bignet fries were just amazing!

We went here as a group of 5 I Paid 7 dollars for a "half" bowl of gumbo which was in the smallest bowl I have ever seen. Afterwards we were told that the bill couldn't be split it could on be 1 tab that could take up to 4 forms of payment. After a while of us doing math to split the ticket evenly the waitor finally said he would split it for us. The service was ok but the small servings and the high prices are absolutely insane. Not to add the already included gratuity that made an 8 dollar tab turn into 15.

This was my first visit to New Orleans, so I'm not a local/culinary expert by any means. However, I had a great breakfast experience. Very polite staff, there's A/C, they accept credit cards, good music and atmosphere, and great beignet fries. Also, excellent spot for people-watching!

Breakfast was awesome, their pancakes are a must! The bartender, Allison, was terrific!! She was extremely friendly and we really enjoyed our conversation with her.
The jumbalya omelet was excellent, so were the beignet fries.
Stopped in for a drink and to cool off from the heat. Our server was very sweet and friendly. Our drinks were refreshing and strong!

This restaurant has a very good location. I thought the Shrimp Po' boy was overpriced. My wife also noticed that the waiters, mostly guys, put the check holders/presenters tucked behind their butts which is kind of unhygienic.

My sister and I came here for breakfast on a Sunday morning. There was no wait, which was awesome. I ordered the sweet cream pancakes with strawberries, which I really liked! The pancakes were huge and very filling. My sister ordered the Jackson Square omelette, which has shrimp and crab in it. The seafood was fresh and yummy, and the side potatoes were tasty and well seasoned. The orange juice was nice and fresh. Our waiter, Dustin, was very friendly and attentive (he is also cute).  Would return!

Decided to try breakfast here on a whim and was very pleased. I thought their breakfast was delicious. It was pretty early and empty when we went so service was very attentive. Having an open air cafe on the square is just tough to beat.
Food was great, portions were more than enough to share; service was excellent. I would definitely recommend this restaurant.

You must get the beignet fries here. They are to die for. Fast service and a great vibe. It's a good quick snack that's across from cafe du monde but not as busy. If you don't want to wait for Cafe Du Monde's sometimes busy line, this place is great.

Sat at the bar for breakfast. Bar tender with green hair didn’t greet us for 5 minutes. She was the only one behind the bar and was making 10 drink tickets for servers and not acknowledging us. We finally ordered drinks then waited another 10 min. I had to ask if we could please put in our food order and she replied “what do you want?”  as if we were annoying her. Food came and she NEVER asked us if we needed anything or if our food was ok. Rudely threw silverware onto the bar top. She made us feel so uncomfortable we didn’t even want to ask for more water !!! She dropped our check and left the bar, never asked how everything was or say thank you. Food was good but that was the worst service I’ve ever received. We tried to saw thank you to the hostess on our way out and she was looking at her phone and ignored us as well.  I never write reviews but the company should know about this one ! Get a friendlier bar tender and a hostess who does the job!

An amazing place for breakfast in the French quarter. They had such amazing coffee, French Market was the coffee served on a beautiful Monday morning. I had the Crab cake eggs Benedict I asked for the sauce on the side. It was such a pleasant breakfast. My mom had a crossiant with coffee. She tends to keep her breakfast small and this place had the perfect options for her and an amazing option for me. A place I'd go to every morning while visiting the French Quarter. Definitely a must to your itinerary. 🥐🍳☕🦀
